  "text": "Selenium is the 34th element on the periodic table and has chemical properties resembling those of sulfur [CITATION_1] . It is an essential micronutrient for animals and microorganisms, , used in the synthesis of the seleno-amino acids selenocysteine and as much as 5 mg Se/kg. Natural waters generally have Se concentrations < 0.01 mg/L but agricultural drainage waters often have Se concentrations of 140 to 1400 mg/L [CITATION_2] .",
